00:00:06.941 --> 00:00:08.676 position:13% line:89% align:start
[helicopter alarm beeping]

00:00:09.677 --> 00:00:11.579 position:33% line:89% align:start
Okay, Ermes,

00:00:11.613 --> 00:00:13.447 position:10% line:83% align:start
how fast is this thing going
right now?

00:00:13.480 --> 00:00:15.583 position:38% line:89% align:start
170? 200?

00:00:15.617 --> 00:00:16.551 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:00:16.584 --> 00:00:18.151 position:27% line:83% align:start
We're getting off
of this thing. Emporio!

00:00:19.621 --> 00:00:21.088 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunts]

00:00:21.121 --> 00:00:22.122 position:27% line:89% align:start
[wind whooshing]

00:00:24.091 --> 00:00:25.793 position:24% line:83% align:start
But when those rods
came into my life,

00:00:25.827 --> 00:00:27.294 position:30% line:83% align:start
when I saw them
for the first time,

00:00:27.327 --> 00:00:29.664 position:24% line:83% align:start
I finally realized
its importance.

00:00:29.697 --> 00:00:31.164 position:16% line:89% align:start
It wasn't about the dude.

00:00:31.198 --> 00:00:34.201 position:19% line:83% align:start
The moon landing was an
achievement for all humanity!

00:00:34.234 --> 00:00:35.937 position:24% line:83% align:start
That day, we humans
conquered the moon

00:00:35.970 --> 00:00:37.471 position:16% line:89% align:start
and our spirits evolved.

00:00:37.505 --> 00:00:41.475 position:7% line:83% align:start
What's truly significant is the
evolution of the human race!

00:00:42.010 --> 00:00:43.176 position:27% line:89% align:start
[lighter clicks]

00:00:43.210 --> 00:00:45.647 position:7% line:89% align:start
You don't gotta worry about me.

00:00:45.680 --> 00:00:47.281 position:7% line:89% align:start
I honestly don't even feel it.

00:00:48.148 --> 00:00:49.717 position:16% line:83% align:start
Compared to all the shit
I've gone through

00:00:49.751 --> 00:00:50.818 position:21% line:89% align:start
to get to the priest,

00:00:50.852 --> 00:00:52.554 position:21% line:89% align:start
this pain is nothing.

00:00:52.587 --> 00:00:56.323 position:38% line:83% align:start
[groans]
You crazy bitch!

00:00:56.356 --> 00:00:58.793 position:24% line:83% align:start
If you're trying to
test my spirit,

00:00:58.826 --> 00:01:00.695 position:10% line:89% align:start
it's way stronger than yours!

00:01:01.328 --> 00:01:03.363 position:16% line:89% align:start
[intense showdown music]

00:01:03.397 --> 00:01:04.566 position:13% line:89% align:start
I'm gonna finish you here!

00:01:04.599 --> 00:01:08.636 position:19% line:83% align:start
Oraa, oraa, oraa, oraa,
oraa, oraa, oraa...

00:01:10.004 --> 00:01:10.672 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gargles]

00:01:10.705 --> 00:01:12.507 position:35% line:83% align:start
Oh shit.
[thuds]

00:01:13.708 --> 00:01:15.208 position:35% line:89% align:start
[groaning]

00:01:15.242 --> 00:01:18.713 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Jolyne!
-Oh yeah! Our girl's alive!

00:01:19.547 --> 00:01:21.148 position:24% line:83% align:start
He must be special
since the priest

00:01:21.181 --> 00:01:22.416 position:24% line:83% align:start
took away the disc
with his memories

00:01:22.449 --> 00:01:25.587 position:13% line:83% align:start
and he decided to keep him
alive in that prison.

00:01:26.420 --> 00:01:27.254 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Rikiel] Weather Forecast.

00:01:28.856 --> 00:01:30.592 position:27% line:89% align:start
[breathes deeply]

00:01:30.625 --> 00:01:33.528 position:10% line:83% align:start
Because he happens to be the
priest's biological brother.

00:01:34.194 --> 00:01:36.463 position:21% line:89% align:start
Let's go to Orlando.

00:01:36.496 --> 00:01:38.365 position:24% line:83% align:start
That's where we'll
find him hiding, right?

00:01:39.901 --> 00:01:42.704 position:33% line:89% align:start
[theme music]

00:03:28.176 --> 00:03:29.811 position:13% line:89% align:start
[ambulance sirens blaring]

00:03:30.410 --> 00:03:31.646 position:24% line:89% align:start
[wheels screeching]

00:03:31.679 --> 00:03:33.313 position:30% line:83% align:start
[medic] Hurry!
Get Surgery Room 3 prepared.

00:03:33.346 --> 00:03:36.150 position:7% line:83% align:start
We've got an eight-year-old boy
in critical condition.

00:03:36.184 --> 00:03:39.120 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Mike's mom wailing]
Mike!

00:03:39.153 --> 00:03:39.887 position:33% line:83% align:start
[Mike's dad]
It's okay. It'll be okay.

00:03:39.921 --> 00:03:41.556 position:21% line:89% align:start
[motor brake squeaks]

00:03:43.725 --> 00:03:45.626 position:33% line:89% align:start
Hey, Jolyne.

00:03:45.660 --> 00:03:47.061 position:19% line:83% align:start
You said this is where
the priest was hiding.

00:03:47.095 --> 00:03:49.496 position:7% line:89% align:start
But this is a fucking hospital?

00:03:50.031 --> 00:03:50.397 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Jolyne] He's here.

00:03:51.733 --> 00:03:53.300 position:27% line:5% align:start
I don't know why,

00:03:53.333 --> 00:03:55.335 position:13% line:5% align:start
but he's definitely waiting
for us inside.

00:03:57.404 --> 00:03:59.306 position:30% line:83% align:start
We're gonna put
an end to this here.

00:04:02.577 --> 00:04:04.512 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh...

00:04:04.545 --> 00:04:06.013 position:24% line:83% align:start
-[Jolyne] Emporio.
-[Emporio] Huh...

00:04:06.881 --> 00:04:08.248 position:30% line:89% align:start
I need a favor.

00:04:08.281 --> 00:04:09.984 position:24% line:89% align:start
This is important.

00:04:10.017 --> 00:04:11.451 position:24% line:83% align:start
I want you to take
my father's disc,

00:04:11.485 --> 00:04:12.887 position:19% line:89% align:start
and deliver it for me.

00:04:12.920 --> 00:04:14.756 position:16% line:89% align:start
If you call this number,

00:04:14.789 --> 00:04:16.691 position:16% line:83% align:start
the Speedwagon Foundation
will come get it.

00:04:21.261 --> 00:04:22.063 position:19% line:89% align:start
I wanna go in with you.

00:04:22.096 --> 00:04:24.532 position:41% line:83% align:start
I know.
But before that,

00:04:24.565 --> 00:04:26.768 position:19% line:83% align:start
I need you to make sure
the disc gets delivered.

00:04:26.801 --> 00:04:28.202 position:24% line:89% align:start
It's all up to you.

00:04:28.236 --> 00:04:30.671 position:7% line:83% align:start
By now, the priest should sense
that I'm getting closer to him.

00:04:30.705 --> 00:04:34.008 position:13% line:83% align:start
I don't wanna be separated
from you right now either,

00:04:34.842 --> 00:04:35.710 position:24% line:89% align:start
but it's necessary.

00:04:37.044 --> 00:04:39.547 position:33% line:89% align:start
Uh... Huh...

00:04:40.715 --> 00:04:42.617 position:19% line:83% align:start
Keep in touch with this
cellphone I took off Rikiel.

00:04:48.956 --> 00:04:50.423 position:19% line:89% align:start
[low suspenseful music]

00:04:52.392 --> 00:04:53.460 position:13% line:89% align:start
[machines beeping steadily]

00:05:01.903 --> 00:05:04.038 position:21% line:89% align:start
Sorry to bother you,

00:05:04.071 --> 00:05:05.206 position:21% line:83% align:start
but I'd like to hear
your opinion

00:05:05.239 --> 00:05:06.607 position:13% line:89% align:start
on something I'm unsure of.

00:05:07.275 --> 00:05:09.342 position:16% line:89% align:start
Particularly, this dish.

00:05:09.376 --> 00:05:10.678 position:16% line:89% align:start
Take a bite if you would.

00:05:10.711 --> 00:05:12.713 position:33% line:83% align:start
I want you to
taste-test it for me.

00:05:13.281 --> 00:05:14.949 position:41% line:89% align:start
Versus.

00:05:14.982 --> 00:05:18.085 position:19% line:89% align:start
[low suspenseful music]

00:05:23.390 --> 00:05:24.625 position:24% line:89% align:start
One bite is enough.

00:05:30.497 --> 00:05:33.901 position:16% line:83% align:start
After you eat it, tell me
what ingredients are inside.

00:05:33.935 --> 00:05:36.369 position:21% line:83% align:start
If there's shellfish,
I can't eat it.

00:05:36.403 --> 00:05:37.470 position:33% line:83% align:start
I'm allergic,
so I would get quite sick.

00:05:42.844 --> 00:05:43.443 position:47% line:89% align:start
Hm.

00:05:44.145 --> 00:05:45.580 position:24% line:89% align:start
This is whitefish.

00:05:46.479 --> 00:05:48.082 position:21% line:89% align:start
Most likely flounder.

00:05:49.317 --> 00:05:51.252 position:24% line:83% align:start
It has been paired
with this flan.

00:05:51.285 --> 00:05:54.188 position:21% line:83% align:start
A delectable pudding
mixed with asparagus

00:05:54.222 --> 00:05:56.456 position:7% line:89% align:start
and mashed-up crab meat inside.

00:05:56.489 --> 00:05:58.458 position:19% line:89% align:start
I detect no shellfish.

00:05:59.426 --> 00:06:00.928 position:35% line:89% align:start
Incredible.

00:06:00.962 --> 00:06:01.494 position:21% line:89% align:start
But hold on a second.

00:06:03.064 --> 00:06:04.497 position:7% line:89% align:start
May I have another small bite,

00:06:04.532 --> 00:06:06.667 position:7% line:83% align:start
but this time with a little dab
of sauce on the side?

00:06:07.635 --> 00:06:08.502 position:21% line:83% align:start
There's a faint scent
from the sauce.

00:06:10.171 --> 00:06:11.939 position:13% line:89% align:start
Judging by the fishy aroma,

00:06:11.973 --> 00:06:14.108 position:10% line:83% align:start
I suspect it's scallop paste
mixed with cream.

00:06:22.984 --> 00:06:25.485 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Versus] How unfortunate.
Just as I thought.

00:06:25.519 --> 00:06:27.487 position:24% line:83% align:start
There are scallops
inside the sauce.

00:06:28.689 --> 00:06:30.490 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Father Pucchi] Is your
shoe size 27 centimeters?

00:06:32.326 --> 00:06:33.527 position:7% line:83% align:start
Pardon me, but could you stand
for a moment?

00:06:35.263 --> 00:06:36.429 position:47% line:89% align:start
Hm?

00:06:36.463 --> 00:06:37.331 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Father Pucchi]
Be careful not to open up

00:06:37.365 --> 00:06:39.000 position:10% line:89% align:start
the bullet wound on your leg.

00:06:39.033 --> 00:06:40.167 position:35% line:89% align:start
Slowly now.

00:06:41.401 --> 00:06:45.373 position:33% line:83% align:start
You're about
181 centimeters tall, yes?

00:06:45.405 --> 00:06:48.175 position:33% line:83% align:start
And you weigh
precisely 72 kilograms.

00:06:48.209 --> 00:06:50.144 position:16% line:89% align:start
Are your clothes size 52?

00:06:51.245 --> 00:06:52.546 position:10% line:83% align:start
And do you tighten your watch
belt on the second hole?

00:06:54.081 --> 00:06:54.815 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

00:06:55.850 --> 00:06:57.985 position:27% line:89% align:start
How interesting.

00:06:59.020 --> 00:07:01.656 position:13% line:83% align:start
Though I'm unable to enjoy
this fine meal,

00:07:01.689 --> 00:07:02.790 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm quite impressed
by your ability

00:07:02.823 --> 00:07:05.159 position:19% line:83% align:start
to pick out the scallop
from the sauce.

00:07:06.459 --> 00:07:09.030 position:19% line:83% align:start
It would appear we have
a similar sense of taste.

00:07:11.132 --> 00:07:13.868 position:19% line:89% align:start
[machine alarm beeping]

00:07:18.438 --> 00:07:20.408 position:24% line:89% align:start
Interesting indeed.

00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:22.576 position:19% line:89% align:start
Tell me, Father Pucchi,

00:07:24.111 --> 00:07:25.813 position:13% line:89% align:start
what are you trying to say?

00:07:25.846 --> 00:07:29.417 position:13% line:83% align:start
You're aware I haven't seen
my own ability yet,

00:07:29.449 --> 00:07:30.450 position:10% line:89% align:start
and plus, I can sense someone

00:07:30.483 --> 00:07:32.452 position:24% line:83% align:start
quickly approaching
our location.

00:07:33.721 --> 00:07:35.523 position:30% line:83% align:start
I want to help
in any way I can.

00:07:36.390 --> 00:07:36.624 position:27% line:89% align:start
What should I do?

00:07:38.059 --> 00:07:38.960 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hmm...

00:07:40.428 --> 00:07:42.296 position:21% line:89% align:start
That can't be helped.

00:07:42.330 --> 00:07:45.099 position:10% line:83% align:start
In fact, their arrival might
actually prove useful to me.

00:07:45.132 --> 00:07:45.900 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Versus's shocked gasp]

00:07:45.933 --> 00:07:48.836 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Mike's mom crying]
Oh, Mike...

00:07:48.869 --> 00:07:50.905 position:41% line:83% align:start
[nurse]
Your son's going to be fine.

00:07:52.073 --> 00:07:53.975 position:19% line:89% align:start
He's really close now.

00:07:55.042 --> 00:07:56.110 position:21% line:89% align:start
He's here somewhere.

00:07:57.712 --> 00:07:59.413 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Father Pucchi] If you're still
unable to see your ability

00:07:59.447 --> 00:08:00.848 position:13% line:83% align:start
then there is nothing else
that can be done.

00:08:02.083 --> 00:08:05.419 position:10% line:83% align:start
Don't struggle against things
beyond your understanding,

00:08:05.453 --> 00:08:06.520 position:33% line:83% align:start
let the power
take its own course.

00:08:09.056 --> 00:08:11.726 position:30% line:83% align:start
If we are going
to make it to heaven,

00:08:11.759 --> 00:08:13.427 position:19% line:83% align:start
you must ally yourself
with the power

00:08:13.461 --> 00:08:15.129 position:10% line:89% align:start
that lies dormant within you.

00:08:16.030 --> 00:08:17.965 position:33% line:83% align:start
And besides,
there's a chance Jolyne

00:08:17.999 --> 00:08:20.034 position:30% line:83% align:start
might overlook
this room entirely.

00:08:21.035 --> 00:08:23.304 position:33% line:83% align:start
Nevertheless,
I decided to order this dish

00:08:23.337 --> 00:08:26.474 position:21% line:83% align:start
because they told me
there'd be no shellfish inside.

00:08:26.507 --> 00:08:28.442 position:30% line:83% align:start
If you'd like,
you may eat it yourself.

00:08:28.476 --> 00:08:30.578 position:30% line:89% align:start
[ominous music]

00:08:32.480 --> 00:08:33.748 position:30% line:89% align:start
Father Pucchi.

00:08:34.281 --> 00:08:35.583 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Versus gasps]

00:08:35.616 --> 00:08:38.285 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Mike] I... I...

00:08:39.954 --> 00:08:42.957 position:33% line:89% align:start
I... I was...

00:08:45.526 --> 00:08:48.129 position:35% line:83% align:start
Look at me,
I was shot to death!

00:08:49.864 --> 00:08:53.167 position:16% line:83% align:start
It was a lot of fun going
for a ride in the ambulance.

00:08:53.200 --> 00:08:55.369 position:16% line:83% align:start
But it was ruined because
my daddy doesn't like me.

00:08:55.403 --> 00:08:58.439 position:7% line:89% align:start
My daddy's the one who shot me.

00:08:58.472 --> 00:08:59.407 position:27% line:89% align:start
[blood sloshing]

00:08:59.440 --> 00:09:01.175 position:41% line:83% align:start
[Mike]
He was trying to kill me!

00:09:01.510 --> 00:09:02.511 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gunshot]

00:09:02.543 --> 00:09:05.780 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[gasps]
-[Mike's mom] Honey? Honey!

00:09:05.813 --> 00:09:06.914 position:21% line:89% align:start
Honey, what happened?

00:09:06.947 --> 00:09:09.316 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Someone was shot!
-[Mike's mom crying]

00:09:09.350 --> 00:09:10.418 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Mike's mom] Oh, God!

00:09:10.451 --> 00:09:13.320 position:19% line:83% align:start
Why... Why did you have
to take him too?

00:09:13.354 --> 00:09:15.956 position:38% line:83% align:start
-No! No!
-[both gasp]

00:09:15.990 --> 00:09:18.192 position:33% line:89% align:start
[eerie music]

00:09:18.225 --> 00:09:21.295 position:24% line:89% align:start
[eerie music rises]

00:09:23.664 --> 00:09:26.967 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Ermes] What the hell?
This hospital room is a mess.

00:09:27.835 --> 00:09:30.004 position:35% line:83% align:start
That priest
must have been in here.

00:09:31.138 --> 00:09:33.841 position:19% line:83% align:start
But now where the fuck
is he hiding?

00:09:33.874 --> 00:09:36.377 position:21% line:83% align:start
Whatever's going on,
I think it's safe to assume

00:09:36.410 --> 00:09:38.513 position:7% line:83% align:start
that the new enemy that's been
hanging around the priest

00:09:38.547 --> 00:09:39.847 position:16% line:89% align:start
is the cause of all this.

00:09:40.781 --> 00:09:42.683 position:19% line:89% align:start
Although, that gunshot

00:09:42.716 --> 00:09:44.785 position:16% line:83% align:start
didn't exactly feel like
a Stand attack.

00:09:44.819 --> 00:09:47.421 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's more like somebody fired
a real bullet.

00:09:47.455 --> 00:09:50.124 position:21% line:83% align:start
And the poor bastard
that got shot,

00:09:50.157 --> 00:09:51.959 position:21% line:89% align:start
who even is that guy?

00:09:51.992 --> 00:09:53.694 position:30% line:83% align:start
Why would he be
the one to get hit?

00:09:53.727 --> 00:09:54.895 position:19% line:89% align:start
I mean, looking at him,

00:09:54.929 --> 00:09:57.431 position:30% line:83% align:start
he seems to be
just a random, ordinary dude!

00:09:57.465 --> 00:09:59.066 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Mike's mom] Oh, honey!

00:09:59.100 --> 00:10:00.468 position:24% line:83% align:start
I need you to hurry
and evacuate

00:10:00.502 --> 00:10:02.504 position:10% line:89% align:start
everyone on this floor. Now!

00:10:02.537 --> 00:10:03.237 position:38% line:89% align:start
Yes, sir.

00:10:04.105 --> 00:10:05.239 position:24% line:83% align:start
Hey! That goes for
you two as well.

00:10:05.272 --> 00:10:07.542 position:19% line:89% align:start
Hurry up and evacuate!

00:10:07.576 --> 00:10:09.076 position:10% line:89% align:start
I'm gonna go call the police.

00:10:11.879 --> 00:10:14.915 position:21% line:83% align:start
[gasps] That's right.
I remember that man now.

00:10:14.949 --> 00:10:17.284 position:7% line:83% align:start
He's the parent of that kid who
was brought in by the ambulance

00:10:17.318 --> 00:10:19.086 position:27% line:83% align:start
when we first got
to this place.

00:10:19.887 --> 00:10:21.755 position:10% line:83% align:start
-Maybe it was a test shot...
-Huh?

00:10:23.958 --> 00:10:25.893 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Jolyne] I have no idea what
kind of ability it could be,

00:10:25.926 --> 00:10:29.063 position:10% line:83% align:start
but if it's someone who just
had their powers awakened,

00:10:30.030 --> 00:10:31.966 position:30% line:83% align:start
they would need
to give it a test drive

00:10:31.999 --> 00:10:33.734 position:30% line:83% align:start
and try it out
on somebody first.

00:10:34.902 --> 00:10:35.537 position:27% line:83% align:start
-[Jolyne grunts]
-[door thudding]

00:10:35.570 --> 00:10:36.637 position:30% line:89% align:start
[ominous music]

00:10:36.670 --> 00:10:39.406 position:27% line:83% align:start
-[wind whooshing]
-[Ermes] Oh, hell nah.

00:10:44.378 --> 00:10:46.347 position:7% line:89% align:start
The priest is moving right now.

00:10:46.380 --> 00:10:47.915 position:21% line:89% align:start
Somewhere down there!

00:10:47.948 --> 00:10:50.619 position:7% line:89% align:start
That bastard's inside the hole!

00:10:50.651 --> 00:10:52.119 position:30% line:83% align:start
I can sense him
getting further away from here.

