Did you see anyone?

00:19:31.005 --> 00:19:33.240 position:24% line:89% align:start
No, I have no clue.

00:19:33.273 --> 00:19:34.341 position:7% line:89% align:start
Besides, even if the cops came,

00:19:34.374 --> 00:19:36.376 position:16% line:83% align:start
they wouldn't be able to
hear us calling

00:19:36.410 --> 00:19:39.080 position:10% line:83% align:start
just like I couldn't hear you
up there earlier.

00:19:39.113 --> 00:19:40.447 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Ermes] How's this plane
down here anyway?

00:19:40.480 --> 00:19:41.716 position:7% line:89% align:start
I didn't see anything like this

00:19:41.749 --> 00:19:43.618 position:13% line:83% align:start
when I was waiting for you
to come out of the hole.

00:19:44.018 --> 00:19:44.317 position:44% line:89% align:start
Oraa!

00:19:46.954 --> 00:19:48.089 position:24% line:83% align:start
[flight attendant]
Excuse me, miss.

00:19:48.122 --> 00:19:49.857 position:24% line:83% align:start
Please refrain from
punching the ceiling.

00:19:49.891 --> 00:19:52.694 position:16% line:83% align:start
If you would kindly take
your seat and wait quietly.

00:19:53.928 --> 00:19:56.229 position:13% line:83% align:start
This plane will be crashing
in less than three minutes.

00:19:56.263 --> 00:19:57.230 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Jolyne and Ermes gasp]

00:19:57.264 --> 00:20:00.300 position:21% line:83% align:start
Okay, then let us see
the pilot.

00:20:00.333 --> 00:20:02.469 position:19% line:83% align:start
We gotta make him land
this plane immediately.

00:20:02.503 --> 00:20:04.939 position:24% line:83% align:start
Now hurry up, lady,
and take us to the cockpit!

00:20:05.707 --> 00:20:07.207 position:38% line:89% align:start
No point.

00:20:07.240 --> 00:20:07.909 position:35% line:89% align:start
[sizzling]

00:20:07.942 --> 00:20:10.845 position:24% line:89% align:start
[foreboding music]

00:20:10.878 --> 00:20:12.046 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Jolyne gasps]

00:20:12.080 --> 00:20:14.082 position:30% line:83% align:start
We weren't able
to land the plane safely.

00:20:14.115 --> 00:20:17.118 position:27% line:83% align:start
That's the reason
why we crashed.

00:20:17.151 --> 00:20:18.953 position:35% line:89% align:start
Holy shit!

00:20:20.220 --> 00:20:23.356 position:21% line:83% align:start
Unfortunately for us,
we all burned to death.

00:20:23.390 --> 00:20:24.625 position:10% line:89% align:start
When the plane crash-landed,

00:20:24.659 --> 00:20:27.128 position:33% line:89% align:start
it exploded.

00:20:27.161 --> 00:20:28.830 position:10% line:89% align:start
And that was when my body...

00:20:28.863 --> 00:20:30.598 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gulping]

00:20:30.631 --> 00:20:33.201 position:24% line:83% align:start
Um, excuse me, sir.
Did you not hear me

00:20:33.233 --> 00:20:34.802 position:21% line:83% align:start
when I told everyone
to turn off

00:20:34.836 --> 00:20:36.804 position:7% line:83% align:start
all of their electronic devices
earlier?

00:20:36.838 --> 00:20:37.839 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasping]

00:20:37.872 --> 00:20:39.907 position:33% line:83% align:start
Could it be?
I... I think I remember this.

00:20:39.941 --> 00:20:43.477 position:7% line:89% align:start
It was Flight 2882, to Dallas.

00:20:43.511 --> 00:20:44.712 position:7% line:89% align:start
Around six or seven years ago,

00:20:44.746 --> 00:20:47.014 position:35% line:83% align:start
it crashed
somewhere near Orlando.

00:20:47.048 --> 00:20:48.583 position:7% line:89% align:start
We're dealing with ghosts here!

00:20:48.616 --> 00:20:50.518 position:7% line:89% align:start
No, we're memories. That's all.

00:20:50.551 --> 00:20:54.354 position:16% line:83% align:start
Remnants of memories that
were recorded by the Earth.

00:20:54.387 --> 00:20:55.489 position:16% line:89% align:start
Are you trying to tell me

00:20:55.523 --> 00:20:57.357 position:21% line:83% align:start
we're actually gonna
crash in this thing?

00:20:59.560 --> 00:21:00.561 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:21:02.897 --> 00:21:06.567 position:13% line:83% align:start
Can you not make this plane
crash happen any faster?

00:21:06.601 --> 00:21:08.202 position:27% line:83% align:start
I've been sensing
Weather Forecast

00:21:08.236 --> 00:21:09.871 position:7% line:89% align:start
getting closer to our position.

00:21:11.038 --> 00:21:12.372 position:27% line:89% align:start
[sirens blaring]

00:21:18.880 --> 00:21:20.081 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Father Pucchi] It appears that
he is drawing

00:21:20.114 --> 00:21:22.550 position:24% line:83% align:start
ever closer toward
this hospital.

00:21:22.583 --> 00:21:25.352 position:10% line:83% align:start
I swear to God, if you don't
shut the fuck up already

00:21:25.385 --> 00:21:27.221 position:19% line:89% align:start
and stop confusing me.

00:21:27.255 --> 00:21:29.557 position:10% line:89% align:start
Huh? Were you speaking to me?

00:21:30.591 --> 00:21:31.391 position:41% line:89% align:start
Uh-huh.

00:21:34.294 --> 00:21:36.264 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Versus] Netherworld's ability
is to excavate

00:21:36.296 --> 00:21:37.698 position:16% line:89% align:start
memories from the ground.

00:21:38.566 --> 00:21:40.367 position:7% line:89% align:start
And this plane is set to crash

00:21:40.400 --> 00:21:43.237 position:21% line:83% align:start
specifically at 21:33
on the dot.

00:21:43.271 --> 00:21:44.272 position:10% line:89% align:start
Also, try not to forget that

00:21:44.304 --> 00:21:46.574 position:27% line:83% align:start
I've capitalized
on this opportunity

00:21:46.607 --> 00:21:49.544 position:16% line:83% align:start
and managed to pull Ermes
into my hole as well.

00:21:49.577 --> 00:21:51.245 position:47% line:89% align:start
Hm.

00:21:51.279 --> 00:21:53.380 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Versus] I have done this
all for you, Father.

00:21:54.115 --> 00:21:55.750 position:16% line:89% align:start
Now just leave it to me.

00:21:57.084 --> 00:21:58.753 position:38% line:83% align:start
-[grunts]
-Huh?

00:21:58.786 --> 00:21:59.620 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:22:00.822 --> 00:22:02.623 position:35% line:89% align:start
[both gasp]

00:22:10.097 --> 00:22:13.601 position:24% line:83% align:start
["Distant Dreamer"
by Duffy playing]

